A question from the kid: &ldquo;Who do you miss more, Manchester or Madrid?&rdquo;<br />
<br />
Cristiano: &ldquo;I miss Madrid more&rdquo;

Zidane on James: &ldquo;I don't know what's going to happen with him. We're here playing and that's the only thing I'm thinking about and nothing else.&rdquo;<br />
<br />
Zidane on Bale: &ldquo;He didn't travel because he wasn't fit. After speaking with the doctors, the best thing was for him to stay in Madrid. He stayed back and is training there. It was a joint decision between the player, medical staff and the coach.&rdquo;

Borja Mayoral: &ldquo;My future? In the end, the decision does not depend exclusively on me, I belong to Real Madrid. There has been talk of joining Real Sociedad and other teams, but Quico and my environment know that my desire was to return here to Levante.&rdquo;<br />
<br />
Borja Mayoral: &ldquo;What made me want to come back here? Many things. This coaching staff makes me improve a lot. I was used to playing another style, but I was able to adapt to the style of Levante. I'm glad I can come back.&rdquo;

Former Brazil U-17s coach Carlos Amadeu: &ldquo;If Rodrygo struggles for opportunities in the first team, he should get himself in the second team and keep on learning his trade there, just like Vinicius did.&rdquo;<br />
<br />
Former Brazil U-17s coach Carlos Amadeu: &ldquo;If Rodrygo and Kubo are fighting for just the one spot, I think it'll be very close. Rodrygo has a tough job on his hands, because Kubo also has bags of ability. They can both operate in a number of roles and boast real quality.&rdquo;
